headline: Accenture awarded $336.83M Air Force contract
summary: Accenture (ACN) Federal Services was awarded a $336.83M cost-plus-fixed-fee, level of effort contract, with cost-reimbursable contract line-item numbers for travel and other direct costs, and a firm-fixed-price contract line-item number for data deliverables. This contract provides for a continuation of maintenance, repair, and overhaul activities and the additions of MRO-Supply. Work will be performed at the contractor’s discretion and is expected to be completed by Oct. 7, 2030. FiY25 capital
